schema:creator: Long, J.D.
schema:description: Built by the Mission Fathers (1775-1800?). Dam some 8' high and 10"-12" thick built of rock and some burned tile with lime mortar. Flume ran from a dam some four miles below the upper one shown and was built of flat burned slabs with semi-circular tile in bottom, all cemented with lime plaster.
